\nWhat makes each person happy can vary dramatically and some people get pleasure from certain tasks, items, or experiences that others completely loathe.  One such instance of this is that certain people are happiest when focusing on their own goals or ideas while others are happiest focusing on others.
his does not make one person more selfish or giving than another.  It just further proves the differences between each and every person.

I believe that most people are happiest when focusing on their own goals. I think that everyone can agree that accomplishing something you put your mind to is an amazing feeling.  Such an accomplishment is usually followed with a huge smile or rush of emotion.  Examples of this would be mastering a certain recipe, going to the gym, or getting a promotion at work / certain grade in school.
